content.problemStatement:
Given a program to check whether the sum of all the elements of an array is divisible by 2 or not.
We have inserted some checkpoints in the given program you must find out the good checkpoint which one must use for debugging the code.
```
#include 

int main()
{
    int val = 0;
    printf("%d = Checkpoint1\n", val);
    int arr[8] = {1,0,1,0,1,1,0,1};
    val = arr[0];
    for(int i=1; i<8; i++)
    {
        val = val + arr[i];
    }
    printf("%d = Checkpoint2\n", val);
    val = val % 2;
    if(val == 1)
    {
        printf("not divisible by 2\n");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("divisible by 2\n");
    }

    return 0;
}

```

